cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object segmentation in natural backgrounds. The use of a novel shape descriptor and bag-of-words approach for object detection suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The dense CRF model used for segmentation may also indicate relevance to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of performance on different datasets suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
